    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for MRL 2. Six factors are appropriately scoped out at MRL 2. Both validation results report satisfactory agreement with their respective comparators: the primary NIH comparison meets the ±25% acceptance criterion at all five CPB operating points, and the secondary RH comparison satisfies RH < 1.0 at all points using the Bludszuweit model. The credibility assessment team concludes that the CFD model has sufficient credibility to support identification of worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device. The overall credibility claim is accepted.",
